doctype html
html.no-js(lang='en')
  head
    meta(charset='utf-8')
    meta(name='viewport', content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0')
    title Enlightened Structures
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='css/foundation.css')
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='css/main.css')
    script(src='js/vendor/modernizr.js')
  body      
    .row
      .small-12.medium-4.large-6.columns.namelogo
        h1 Enlightened Structures
    .hero
      .row
        .large-12.columns.intro-text
          p
            | Projects Creating the Future of Humanity
    .row.work
      hr
      .large-12.columns
        h4 About
        p
          | Enlightened Structures is a new show exploring the pioneers in innovating 
          | technological, social, and spiritual systems designed to upgrade the adjacent possible, 
          | and bootstrap a world of abundance which values every creator as a valuable collaborator.

    .row.about
      .medium-6.large-8.columns
        h4 Harlan T Wood
        p
          | Harlan is a core creator and cofounder of the 
          a(href="http://core.enlightenedstructure.net/") Enlightened Structure 
          | projects, 
          | which is holding visions for, and relentlessly prototyping, global-scale collaboration, 
          | universal information visualization and navigation systems, distributed trust systems, 
          | and semantic graph-shaped blockchains upon which to build all the rest.
        p
          | Harlan brings a career of practical software development together with a 
          | diverse background including years of deep training in meditation, personal growth, 
          | and transformational work in a variety of systems. 
          | His recent work includes Technical Architect of 
          a(href="http://superluminal.is/") Superluminal Systems
          , 
          | creators of the 
          a(href="http://academy.resonance.is/") Resonace Academy
          | .  
      .medium-6.large-4.columns
        img(src='img/harlan.jpg')

    .row.about
      .medium-6.large-8.columns
        h4 Steven Starr
        p Steven has spent many years on the alignment of media, technology and storytelling. A co-founder of Noomap, a radical new ‘global brain’ approach to the Internet, Steven pioneered creator sustainability with Revver, grassroots journalism with LA.IndyMedia, P2P with Freenet Project and Uprizer, and co-creative storytelling with StudioOccupy and CitizenGlobal.
        p Steven produced the award-winning global water crisis documentary FLOW, co-executive-produced The Garden, the Academy Award-nominated urban farming doc , and ran KPFK-FM, the largest progressive radio signal in the US.
        p Earlier, he wrote and directed independent film, produced network television, and ran William Morris Agency’s New York film operation. Steven started his career working on concerts for Bob Marley & the Wailers, holds a Master’s Degree in Spiritual Psychology, and he’s served on multiple boards including the Center for Integral Wisdom and San Francisco Film Society.  
      .medium-6.large-4.columns
        img(src='img/steven.jpg')


